  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Hu\u00e1nuco, Peru?",
  "response": "When visiting Hu\u00e1nuco, Peru, here are some lesser-known sights to explore:\n\n1. Archaeological Sites:\n- Hu\u00e1nuco Pampa (an important Inca administrative center)\n- Kotosh archaeological site (featuring ancient religious temples)\n\n2. Natural Attractions:\n- Tingo Mar\u00eda National Park\n- Carpish Mountain Range\n- Le\u00f3n Lake\n- Thermal springs near the city\n\n3. Cultural Locations:\n- Casa de la Cultura Julio C. Tello\n- Regional Historical Museum\n- Sanctuary of Santa Mar\u00eda Magdalena\n- Local indigenous markets\n\n4. Nearby Points of Interest:\n- Pozuzo (a historic German settlement)\n- Cayumba Canyon\n- La Morada del Oso (Bear's Dwelling) ecological reserve\n\n5. Less Touristy Historical Sites:\n- Jos\u00e9 de San Mart\u00edn House\n- Old colonial architecture in the city center\n- Puente Calicanto (historic stone bridge)\n\nThese attractions offer a mix of archaeological, natural, and cultural experiences that are often overlooked by typical tourists. They provide insight into the region's rich history and diverse landscape.\n\nKeep in mind that some locations might require local guides or specific transportation arrangements.",
